.TH VPI 1 "@CMAKE_BUILD_DATE@" "VPI @PROJECT_VERSION@" "Versa Package Installer"
.SH NAME
vpi \- Versa Package Installer
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B vpi
[\fIOPTIONS\fR] \fICOMMAND\fR [\fIARGUMENTS\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
VPI is a cross-platform package manager that installs packages from the Versa registry at versas.my.id.
Packages are distributed as .vers files (renamed ZIP archives) containing a vers.json manifest.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B install \fIpackage\fR
Download and install a package from versas.my.id/package/<name>.vers
.TP
.B remove \fIpackage\fR
Uninstall a previously installed package.
.TP
.B update \fIpackage\fR
Update an installed package to its latest version.
.TP
.B list
List all installed packages with version, developer, and size.
.TP
.B view \fIpackage\fR
Show detailed metadata of an installed package.
.TP
.B search \fIquery\fR
Search for packages on the versas.my.id registry.
.TP
.B info \fIpackage\fR
Show remote package details before installing.
.TP
.B cache [\fIsubcommand\fR]
Manage the local package cache. Subcommands: clear, size.
.TP
.B version
Display the VPI version.
.TP
.B help
Show usage information.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B --verbose
Enable detailed output including file listing and HTTP info.
.TP
.B --no-color
Disable ANSI color output.
.TP
.B --force
Skip confirmation prompts and force operations.
.TP
.B --dry-run
Simulate operations without making any changes.
.SH VERS PACKAGE FORMAT
A .vers file is a standard ZIP archive renamed with the .vers extension.
It MUST contain a \fBvers.json\fR file at the root level with these fields:
.PP
.RS 4
.nf
{
  "nama":      "package-name",
  "versi":     "1.0.0",
  "developer": "Developer Name",
  "lisensi":   "MIT"
}
.fi
.RE
.PP
Optional fields: description, homepage.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.local/share/vpi/packages/
Installed packages (Linux)
.TP
.I ~/Library/Application Support/vpi/packages/
Installed packages (macOS)
.TP
.I %APPDATA%\\vpi\\packages\\
Installed packages (Windows)
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B XDG_DATA_HOME
Override default install directory on Linux.
.TP
.B XDG_CACHE_HOME
Override default cache directory on Linux.
.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Install a package:
.RS 4
vpi install mypackage
.RE
.PP
List all installed packages:
.RS 4
vpi list
.RE
.PP
View package details:
.RS 4
vpi view mypackage
.RE
.PP
Remove a package:
.RS 4
vpi remove mypackage
.RE
.SH AUTHOR
Versas Team <contact@versas.my.id>
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR curl (1),
.BR zip (1)
